discussion.content: The SID for the Guest account always ends in 501. You'll also find SIDs on every installation of Windows which correspond to certain built-in accounts.

choices.A: He needs to gain physical access.
choices.C: He already has admin privileges, as shown by the "501" at the end of the SID.
choices.D: He needs to disable antivirus protection.

Elliot is in the process of exploiting a web application that uses SQL as a back-end database. He is determined that the application is vulnerable to SQL injection and has introduced conditional timing delays into injected queries to determine whether they are successful. What type of SQL injection is Elliot most likely performing?

comments.content: We love you Elliot and MR.ROBOT, too.

discussion.content: Blind SQL injection is a type of SQL injection attack where the attacker indirectly discovers information by analyzing server reactions to injected SQL queries, even though injection results are not visible. Blind SQL injection attacks are used against web applications that are vulnerable to SQL injection but don’t directly reveal information. While more time-consuming than regular SQL injection, blind SQL injection attacks can be automated to map out the database structure and extract sensitive information from the database server.

/var/log/btmp: keeps a note of all failed login attempts.
/var/log/utmp: current login state by user.
/var/log/wtmp: record of each login/logout.
/var/log/lastlog: holds every user’s last login. A binary file you can read via lastlog command.
